Kowloon's Jade Magistracy handles necromancer registration under the Covenant Crisis Prevention framework, specifically provisions addressing practitioners whose work could produce unregistered transitional-status entities during a crisis event. The color jurisdiction system assigns necromantic practice to Indigo oversight — anomalous spiritual phenomena — with a secondary Gold filing requirement for any practice creating entities capable of independent movement in public spaces. The Magistracy's primary concern is contagion risk: a necromancer who loses control of an undead unit during a covenant crisis situation creates a compound emergency. Registration requires practitioners to maintain a bond sufficient to cover emergency containment costs, effectively pricing out practitioners without institutional backing. Kowloon's Neon Covenant mythology frames unlicensed undead as social failure — not supernatural evil but institutional breakdown made visible.

flags KIESS
