A Khenari necromancer operating under Midgaard's Temple Licensing Compact occupies deeply contested ground: Khenari death doctrine requires the nine lawful descents for proper passage, while necromantic practice fundamentally disrupts the departure rite's completion. In Midgaard, this produces a Khenari who views each undead as an incomplete descent — a being arrested mid-procedure, a gap in the death-ledger that violates both civic registry (unregistered transitional status) and sacred law (descent interrupted). The Lantern Registry classifies undead under non-standard sentience provisions; Khenari clerics have filed formal objections arguing that classification normalizes descent-interruption. A Khenari necromancer specifically navigates this by treating the raising process as an extended descent procedure — documentation-intensive, ritually framed, and controversial even within Khenari communities.

