Umbral practitioners experience the compact counterparties whose nature Warlock doctrine disputes — entities of shadow and entropy that Warlock practice names. Necromancer practice works with death-energy that Umbral traditions locate in the same metaphysical register as shadow. In Kowloon, where the Jade Magistracy's Indigo jurisdiction covers anomalous spiritual phenomena, an Umbral necromancer operates at the intersection of two registered categories. The Magistracy's response is to require dual filing under both Indigo (spiritual) and Viridian (shadow-practice) jurisdictions, with a coordination officer assigned to handle cases where the two jurisdictions produce conflicting requirements. Umbral necromancers in Kowloon tend to experience the death-energy they work with as continuous with the absence-energy their racial heritage provides direct access to — less a separate domain of practice than a more complete application of the same underlying orientation toward what is not there.

